I"á<h4 id="bycolors-kyoto-meet-taiwan">byCOLORS Kyoto meet Taiwan</h4>

<p>Role - Technologist</p>

<p>Responsibility</p>

<ul>
  <li>Color sensor build</li>
  <li>Concept ideation</li>
  <li>Interactive display software (Openframeworks)</li>
  <li>Porject management</li>
  <li>Client communication</li>
</ul>

<p>To celebrate Kyoto based coffee and shop ã‚¿ã‚¤ãƒ å ‚â€™s 2 year anniversary, I partnered with designer Hsiao-Han Ni and photographer Chih-Kang Hsu to create an interactive game that connect Kyoto and Taiwan by colors. The system uses AS73211 True color sensor to trigger a rear projected animation. The visitor can play the game by holding a colored woodblock to the screen and it triggers the video and images of where this particular color can be found in both Kyoto and Taiwan. The experience was simple but quite poetic and beautiful.</p>

